The `simp` tactic will expand the definition of `appendLists`, and then `aesop` will solve the resulting equality by induction.
The induction will be on the structure of `as`.
Base case: `as = []`.
Left side: `appendLists (appendLists [] bs) cs = appendLists bs cs`
Right side: `appendLists [] (appendLists bs cs) = appendLists bs cs`
These are equal.

Inductive step: Assume `as = a :: as'`.
Left side: `appendLists (appendLists (a :: as') bs) cs`
